  "prompt": "My friend block a person on what's app how could I know really he is blocked?",
  "response": "If your friend has blocked someone on WhatsApp, there are a few indicators that can suggest this, although there is no definitive way for someone outside the conversation to know for sure. Here are some signs that may indicate that a person has been blocked:\n\n1. **No Last Seen or Online Status**: If you can't see the person's last seen or online status in the chat window, it could be a sign that they have blocked you. However, this feature can also be changed in privacy settings.\n\n2. **Profile Picture and Status Updates**: If you can no longer see the person's profile picture or status updates, it may indicate that you've been blocked. Again, they may have simply chosen to make this information private.\n\n3. **Single Grey Checkmark**: When you send a message to someone who has blocked you, it will show only a single grey checkmark, indicating that the message was sent but not delivered. If the recipient has not blocked you, the checkmarks will turn blue once the message is read (if read receipts are enabled).\n\n4. **Unable to Make Calls**: If you try to make a voice or video call via WhatsApp and it doesn't go through, this may also indicate that you've been blocked.\n\n5. **Inability to Add to Groups**: If you try to add the person to a group chat and see a message indicating that you do not have permission to add that person, it may imply that you have been blocked.\n\nIt\u2019s important to note that these signs are not definitive proof that someone has been blocked. They can also occur due to other reasons, such as changes in privacy settings or network issues.",
